rockets.title: Falcon 9
rockets.short_description: A reusable two-stage rocket by SpaceX.
rockets.detailed_description: The Falcon 9 is a partially reusable launch vehicle designed and manufactured by SpaceX for reliable and safe transport of satellites and cargo into orbit. It features reusability in its first stage which drastically reduces the cost of space missions.

rockets.title: Saturn V
rockets.detailed_description: The Saturn V was the launch vehicle that enabled NASA to send astronauts to the Moon as part of the Apollo program. It remains the tallest, heaviest, and most powerful rocket ever brought to operational status.

rockets.title: Atlas V
rockets.detailed_description: The Atlas V is an expendable launch vehicle developed by United Launch Alliance (ULA). It's known for its reliability and is used for a variety of missions, including government, commercial, and interplanetary payloads.

rockets.title: Ariane 5
rockets.detailed_description: The Ariane 5, developed by Arianespace, is a powerful rocket used primarily to launch commercial satellites into geostationary orbit. It is renowned for its precision and has a strong safety record.

rockets.title: Delta IV Heavy
rockets.short_description: One of the most powerful rockets in operation.
rockets.detailed_description: The Delta IV Heavy is a heavy-lift launch vehicle developed by United Launch Alliance. It is capable of delivering massive payloads to orbit and is often used for national security missions.

rockets.title: Long March 5
rockets.short_description: China's heavy-lift rocket for major space missions.
rockets.detailed_description: The Long March 5 is part of China's powerful family of rockets used to launch heavy satellites and deep space probes. It is integral to China’s lunar and Mars exploration missions.

rockets.title: Electron
rockets.short_description: A small satellite launch vehicle by Rocket Lab.
rockets.detailed_description: The Electron rocket is a lightweight launch system created by Rocket Lab for launching small satellites to low Earth orbit. It’s designed to make space more accessible for startups and researchers.

rockets.title: Starship
rockets.detailed_description: Starship is a revolutionary launch system developed by SpaceX to carry both crew and cargo to Earth orbit, the Moon, and Mars. It is designed to be fully reusable and handle massive payloads.

rockets.title: Soyuz
rockets.detailed_description: The Soyuz rocket is one of the oldest and most reliable launch vehicles still in operation. It has been used for decades to transport astronauts and cosmonauts to the International Space Station.

drones.title: MQ-9 Reaper
drones.detailed_description: The MQ-9 Reaper is an unmanned aerial vehicle developed by General Atomics for the U.S. Air Force. It is capable of remote controlled or autonomous flight and is primarily used for surveillance and precision strikes.

drones.title: DJI Mavic Air 2
drones.short_description: A consumer drone with advanced camera features.
drones.detailed_description: The DJI Mavic Air 2 is a compact drone that delivers excellent image quality and intelligent features. It includes 48MP still images, 4K video, and a flight time of up to 34 minutes, making it ideal for enthusiasts and professionals alike.

drones.title: Skydio 2
drones.short_description: An AI-powered drone with autonomous flight.
drones.detailed_description: The Skydio 2 uses advanced AI and obstacle avoidance to follow subjects with high precision. It's ideal for action sports and hands-free filming without manual piloting.

drones.title: Autel EVO II
drones.short_description: 8K camera drone with long flight time.
drones.detailed_description: The Autel EVO II boasts an 8K camera, 40-minute flight time, and robust obstacle avoidance. It’s built for high-resolution aerial photography and mapping.

drones.title: RQ-4 Global Hawk
drones.detailed_description: The RQ-4 Global Hawk is a high-altitude, long-endurance unmanned aerial vehicle used by the U.S. Air Force for intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance missions around the world.

drones.title: Bayraktar TB2
drones.short_description: A combat drone developed by Turkey.
drones.detailed_description: The Bayraktar TB2 is a medium-altitude long-endurance (MALE) unmanned combat aerial vehicle (UCAV) capable of remotely controlled or autonomous flight operations. It's known for its battlefield impact.

planes.title: Boeing 747
planes.detailed_description: The Boeing 747, commonly referred to as the 'Queen of the Skies', revolutionized air travel with its capacity and long-range capabilities. It has been widely used for commercial flights and cargo transport.

planes.title: F-22 Raptor
planes.detailed_description: The Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor is a cutting-edge tactical fighter aircraft that combines stealth, speed, agility, and situational awareness. It is considered one of the most advanced aircraft in service.

planes.title: Concorde
planes.detailed_description: The Concorde was a British-French turbojet-powered supersonic airliner that could cruise at over twice the speed of sound. It was used for transatlantic flights and is an icon of aviation history.

planes.title: Airbus A380
planes.detailed_description: The Airbus A380 is a double-deck, wide-body aircraft capable of carrying over 800 passengers. It was designed for long-haul international travel and offers luxurious comfort.

planes.title: Cessna 172
planes.detailed_description: The Cessna 172 Skyhawk is one of the most produced aircraft in history. Known for its reliability and ease of use, it is widely used for pilot training and personal flying.

planes.title: Lockheed SR-71 Blackbird
planes.detailed_description: The SR-71 Blackbird was a long-range, advanced, strategic reconnaissance aircraft capable of flying at Mach 3. It was used during the Cold War to collect intelligence and evade enemy missiles.

planes.title: Boeing 737
planes.detailed_description: The Boeing 737 is one of the best-selling commercial aircraft. It is widely used for short- to medium-haul flights and is a staple in airline fleets globally.

planes.title: Airbus A320
planes.detailed_description: The Airbus A320 is a modern, fuel-efficient aircraft that serves as a backbone for many airlines worldwide. It introduced fly-by-wire controls to commercial aviation.

planes.title: F-35 Lightning II
planes.detailed_description: The F-35 Lightning II is a fifth-generation fighter designed for stealth, speed, and versatility. It serves multiple branches of the U.S. military and allies across the globe.

planes.title: McDonnell Douglas DC-10
planes.short_description: A wide-body airliner with three engines.
planes.detailed_description: The DC-10 was used for long-haul flights during the 1970s and 80s. It’s known for its distinctive tri-jet configuration and played a vital role in the growth of global air travel.

planes.title: Beechcraft King Air
planes.detailed_description: The King Air is known for its comfort, reliability, and versatility. It is often used for corporate travel, air ambulance services, and pilot training.

planes.title: B-2 Spirit
planes.short_description: A stealth bomber with flying wing design.
planes.detailed_description: The B-2 Spirit is a long-range, heavy strategic bomber capable of penetrating dense anti-aircraft defenses. It features low observable stealth technology and is used by the U.S. Air Force.

planes.title: Lockheed C-130 Hercules
planes.detailed_description: The C-130 Hercules is used for cargo transport, medical evacuation, and disaster relief. It is known for its rugged design and ability to operate in harsh environments.

planes.title: De Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter
planes.short_description: A short takeoff and landing aircraft.
planes.detailed_description: The DHC-6 Twin Otter is ideal for remote area operations and is used for everything from skydiving to inter-island flights. It’s rugged and adaptable.
